  "texts": [
    "The result, they explained, is that generative AI has obliged them to \"take a closer look at my learning objectives\" and \"then analyze, what are the things that I care about [the students learning]?\"",
    "This instructor recognized their students had declining skills in writing pseudocode, for example, due to AI use, but ultimately decided, \"I didn't care in the context of my course if they lost that skill.\"",
    "They added, though, \"That only makes sense in the context of my course though, whereas in other courses, I would not be okay with that.\"",
    "They emphasized that generative AI is \"impacting what the students are learning\" and that instructors may \"need to change what [they] are doing to adapt to this.\"",
    "In other words, instructors might be best served in altering their learning objectives in certain cases, asking themselves the question of what skills or knowledge are most worth teaching given AI's existence."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}